main event: Two unidentified objects were observed in the sky for four minutes by a housewife in Ellensburg, Washington, on October 5, 1955.
interesting points: The objects were observed using binoculars,The observation was conducted during daylight hours,The objects appeared banded together with a red band,There was no photograph included in the report,The witness speculated the objects might be balloons based on their appearance.
sighted object: two unidentified objects in the sky
